                            Embassy in China</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v10</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d688</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">688</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-03-21T14:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-03-21T14:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-21T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="688" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d688">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3–2146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in China</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-21T14:00:00-05:00">March 21, 1946—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>505. Board Directors Eximbank on Mar 20, 1946 approved renewal undisbursed
                    balance 50 Million Dollar loan to Central Bank of China <pb facs="0978" n="968" xml:id="pg_968"/> under agreement dated Feb. 4, 1941.<note n="98" xml:id="d688fn98">Further details of this agreement are found in a note from
                        the Chinese Ambassador, January 6, 1941, <ref target="frus1941v05#pg_593">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1941, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 593</ref>.</note> Undisbursed balance of
                    $9,204,706.78 renewed for period 12 months ending Dec. 31, 1946.<note n="99" xml:id="d688fn99">In his note of March 29 the Chinese Ambassador informed
                        the Secretary of State that his Government had authorized extension of this
                        agreement to December 31, 1946 (893.51/3–2946).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
